def genres_count(column):
    
    data = MOVIES_PROFIT_df[column].str.cat(sep = '|')
    
    
    data = pd.Series(data.split('|'))
    count = data.value_counts(ascending = False)
    
    return count

## Conclusions After analyzed the data, I discovered that the factors that help make the film a success. A very important factor is genre of movie and The best genre is Drama, Comedy or Action. One of the factors is also movie time ، and The best time is 120 minutes. One of the most important factors is the movie budget ، Most successful movie have a budget of 200-300 million dollars ## limitations: the budget and revenue column does not have a currency unit but it is possible that each movie have a different budget in different currency according to which country the movie is produced in even though dropping the rows with missing values also has affected the overall analysis and some columns contain multi value
